Ghanaian super actress, Yvonne Nelson has weighed in on reasons people get married. The actress took to her Twitter handle to express opinion on why people marry their respective partners. “Some marry for the money, others for a passport, others for kids, others because of a banging body, etc errmm,” she listed.   BBNaija’s Rico Swarvey says tattoos scare men from single…     Regina Daniels gets two new tattoos     Davido, Adekunle Gold headline Pharrel William’s Something…   The ‘Fifty Fity’ actress listed different reasons people get married but ended her tweet with rhetoric asking if people still marry because of love. She wondered: “Do peeps still marry because they love each other or because one is intelligent? Or does everyone now have an agenda?” The actress recently announced plans to release her new feature film entitled ‘Fifty Fity’ on May 21, 2022. The film, which has been in post-production for some months, features John Dumelo, Majid Michel and Anthony Woode, including her.